{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-blog-js","path":"/blog/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"author":{"name":"Yves Gurcan","twitter":"https://twitter.com/yvesgurcan"}}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"excerpt":"From the user perspective, the programming language you are using to build your website does not make much of a difference. Provided that your code compiles down to HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, your users don’t care or even know if you’re using Wordpress, .NET, or React. However, from a developer perspective, the technology you chose is everything. A…","fields":{"slug":"/choosing-the-right-technology/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"May 04, 2020","title":"","image":"tools.png"}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Now more than ever, building a website that follows the guidelines of responsive design is critical. With the variety of electronic devices on the market, having a website that looks good on all screens will help you reach more users. Writing hacks in your code to detect if your user is browsing with an iPhone or an Android is simply not enough…","fields":{"slug":"/think-responsive-with-flexbox/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"April 20, 2020","title":"","image":"responsive.png"}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"With time, it’s natural to forget that a web application means nothing without users. Development might focus on cosmetic changes or swapping technologies under the hood. However, without any substantial improvement for your users, the value of changing the layout of your website or breaking down a monolithic application is questionable. Even worse…","fields":{"slug":"/user-experience-is-everything/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"April 11, 2020","title":"","image":"user-experience.jpg"}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Iterating quickly is a strength when your engineers are experimenting with ideas. However, as soon as a project is taking off, it becomes vital to put best practices in place so that the code can stay maintainable. Why? Because the code that your engineers are writing in a rush today might very well be your tech debt tomorrow. In other words, the…","fields":{"slug":"/adopting-best-practices-is-an-investment/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"April 04, 2020","title":"","image":"code-snippet.png"}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Once a website is ready and online, it might be tempting to simply let it be. The website serves its purpose and is updated from time to time. Nice and easy. However, the problem of a website is that it can not be left alone once it’s online. Why? Well, unfortunately, there are people on the internet who spend a lot of time and resources to find…","fields":{"slug":"/maintaining-your-website/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"March 30, 2020","title":"","image":"npm-audit.png"}}}]},"allFile":{"nodes":[{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"originalName":"npm-audit.png","base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.506666666666667,"src":"/static/03b2c5af6de31c87fd9f9ace0cbb87e7/70753/npm-audit.png","srcSet":"/static/03b2c5af6de31c87fd9f9ace0cbb87e7/7360a/npm-audit.png 188w,\n/static/03b2c5af6de31c87fd9f9ace0cbb87e7/bf027/npm-audit.png 375w,\n/static/03b2c5af6de31c87fd9f9ace0cbb87e7/70753/npm-audit.png 614w","sizes":"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px"}}},{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"originalName":"tools.png","base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.506666666666667,"src":"/static/677d5cddb9c5b4a2405759f24f6d92a4/f69d6/tools.png","srcSet":"/static/677d5cddb9c5b4a2405759f24f6d92a4/7360a/tools.png 188w,\n/static/677d5cddb9c5b4a2405759f24f6d92a4/bf027/tools.png 375w,\n/static/677d5cddb9c5b4a2405759f24f6d92a4/f69d6/tools.png 704w","sizes":"(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px"}}},{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"originalName":"user-experience.jpg","base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.506666666666667,"src":"/static/09e2f18428acee23d9763d3e82a42a68/d6322/user-experience.jpg","srcSet":"/static/09e2f18428acee23d9763d3e82a42a68/6b44e/user-experience.jpg 188w,\n/static/09e2f18428acee23d9763d3e82a42a68/2d2ed/user-experience.jpg 375